Anyone experienced a blackout before? In HDB in your own house 🥲
Only your unit  neighbour’s unit is fine
Anyone know who to call or what to do? 🥹
If u can ask here  means u got access to google
Go to your switch box.see is it one of the switched jumped.If yes  keep it off and turn on the main
Generally it is likely one of the circuits in your ELCB/breaker
If everything is turned back on and nothing comes on  check the mains incoming where the metre is.. there are another 2 breakers there

If it trips again after turning on the mains start isolating the switch circuits in the unit by turning all off and after 10 mins  turn on the breakers check that nothing trips.. then individually area by area turn on your switch sockets again..
Once it trips again  either an appliance or a switch has issues. Isolate those and get someone who knows how to trace those to take a look.. usually it's mostly an appliance issue
